        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2984618554" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8660898945137295491">This book is an emotional, educational eye opener for everyone to read. It’s so well written, it behooves anyone involved with cancer patients, even student nurses and beginning caregivers that enter into the job market, to read this book. It’s beautifully written by someone who has personal experiences and who has spoken with so many cancer patients and caregivers about any type of cancer. It is not just for people with cancer, it could also be understood by people suffering from other terminal</span>
  <span id="freeText8660898945137295491" style="display:none">This book is an emotional, educational eye opener for everyone to read. It’s so well written, it behooves anyone involved with cancer patients, even student nurses and beginning caregivers that enter into the job market, to read this book. It’s beautifully written by someone who has personal experiences and who has spoken with so many cancer patients and caregivers about any type of cancer. It is not just for people with cancer, it could also be understood by people suffering from other terminal or debilitating illnesses, people who are disabled, and even by persons who are aging. <br /><br />I just loved the book and could not put it down until I finished it. I have read it twice and the second time I read it to my husband so he could learn from it as well. I really feel this book should be on the student curriculum for every health care provider to read. </span>
