<div id="review_2983136764" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2983136764" />
    <a title="Hanna Serdynski" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/102979667-hanna-serdynski"><img alt="Hanna Serdynski" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2983136764?book_show_action=true">Sep 19, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hanna Serdynski" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hanna Serdynski" href="/user/show/102979667-hanna-serdynski">Hanna Serdynski</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2983136764" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15680896445361333437">A book that is long overdue. Providing insight with talented writing and personal experience, Lynda sheds truth on a terrible disease. Every healthy person who reads this will leave each page assessing their interactions, effort, and connections, to whoever they thought of when they picked up this book. It is honest learning, and things that needed to be said. It is a powerful piece of work that bridges the gap between terminal disease and connection.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


