<div id="review_4100533425" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4100533425" />
    <a title="Valery" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4013735-valery"><img alt="Valery" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1480691033p2/4013735.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4100533425?book_show_action=true">Jul 07, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Valery" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Valery" href="/user/show/4013735-valery">Valery</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4100533425" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7341812843680686787">Voices of Cancer: What We Really Want, What We Really Need by Lynda Wolters is an eye-opening book and one that will certainly help anyone with cancer or those who are caring for or know a cancer patient. The author is open and honest about her own experiences and relays them well in this book. This serves as solid inspiration for those traveling the cancer path in life. Through sharing conversations with others going through a cancer diagnosis, this is a helpful book and one that can serve as a</span>
  <span id="freeText7341812843680686787" style="display:none">Voices of Cancer: What We Really Want, What We Really Need by Lynda Wolters is an eye-opening book and one that will certainly help anyone with cancer or those who are caring for or know a cancer patient. The author is open and honest about her own experiences and relays them well in this book. This serves as solid inspiration for those traveling the cancer path in life. Through sharing conversations with others going through a cancer diagnosis, this is a helpful book and one that can serve as a sounding board for patients and their families and friends. A highly accessible book, this will resonate, inspire, dispel fear and even encourage open conversation and communication around a difficult topic. Highly recommend. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7341812843680686787" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


