<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer14183884511498614489">Lynda Wolters was born and raised in a tiny farming community of 400 in northern Idaho. She worked on the family farm until graduating high school where she moved to New York and then on to Las Vegas to complete her schooling. <br/><br/>She moved back to Idaho to raise her three sons and work as a paralegal. She and her husband continue to live in Idaho and work hard to keep their long-haired miniature dach</span>
  <span id="freeText14183884511498614489" style="display:none">Lynda Wolters was born and raised in a tiny farming community of 400 in northern Idaho. She worked on the family farm until graduating high school where she moved to New York and then on to Las Vegas to complete her schooling. <br /><br />She moved back to Idaho to raise her three sons and work as a paralegal. She and her husband continue to live in Idaho and work hard to keep their long-haired miniature dachshund, Tucker “Bug,” in treats and toys.<br /><br />Lynda enjoys ballroom and swing dancing, horseback riding, and white water rafting. She volunteers for Epic Experience, a camp for adult survivors and thrivers of cancer.<br /><br />Lynda was diagnosed with stage 4 terminal mantle cell lymphoma in August 2016.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="14183884511498614489" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

